 <purpose>
	<p>
		This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of assembly relationships.
	</p>
	<p>
   		This edition incorporates modifications to the previous edition listed below.
	</p>
	<p>
		The following ARM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been modified:
	</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Assembly_component_relationship;</li>
			<li>Component_upper_level_identification.</li>
		</ul>
	
	<p>
		The following ARM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been added:
	</p>
   		<ul>
   			<li>Product_occurrence_definition_relationship;</li>
   			<li>assembly_component_relationship_constraint.</li>
   		</ul>
   	<p>
		The following ARM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been removed:
	</p>
   		<ul>
   			<li>USE FROM Value_with_unit_arm.</li>
   		</ul>
	<p>
 		In addition, modifications have been made to the mapping specification, 
		the MIM schema and the EXPRESS-G diagrams to reflect and be consistent with the modifications of the ARM.
	</p>
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
      <li>specification of the use of a product version as a component of an assembly;</li>
      <li>specification of a parent-child assembly relationship;</li>
      <li>identification of a component of an assembly with respect to an upper level in the assembly structure;</li>
      <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="generic_product_occurrence:1_scope">Generic product occurrence</module_ref>, ISO/CD-TS 10303-1762.</li>
   </inscope>

 <outscope>
 <li>characterization of the position of a component in an assembly;
 <note>This aspect is specified in the Contextual shape positioning module.</note>
      </li>
 <li>characterization of a component quantity with a qualified quantity or a quantity range.</li>
 </outscope>
